      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## failure"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import {getFailObject, getOrElse, getOrDefault, failure} from \"system://core\"",
        "gD(v) {",
        "    getOrDefault(??v, 42);",
        "}",
        "gE(v) {",
        "    getOrElse(??v, f => failure(\"failed with ${context}\", getFailObject(f).message));",
        "}",
        "{}",
        "console.log(\"getOrDefault(x,42)\", gD(1),gD(undef), gD(failure(\"error\")));",
        "console.log(\"getOrElse(x,failFunc)\", gE(1), gE(undef), ??gE(failure(\"error\")));",
        "console.log(\"getOrElse(x,getMessage)\", getOrElse(failure(\"hibauzenet\"), f=>getFailObject(??f).message  ));"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "`toFailure(arg, msg)` converts the parameter to a failure like in Promise rejections:",
        "* if arg is a failure it is returned as is",
        "* otherwise creates a failure with `arg` as reason"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import {toFailure, getFailObject} from \"system://core\"",
        "{}",
        "$log(toFailure(#{message: 42}, \"alma\"), undef, failure(#{message: \"42\"}));",
        "$log(toFailure(\"alma\"), undef, failure(\"alma\"));",
        "getFailObject(toFailure(\"alma\")).reason"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Iter.iterable",
        "",
        "Iter.iterable makes an iterable from a function returning na iterator. In fact function is only evaluted when iterator is asked for. Ideal for wrapping generators calls into repeatble iteration"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "*gener(from, to) { ",
        "    for(;from<to; ++from) ",
        "        yield from;",
        "}",
        "const range0To10 = Iter.iterable(gener, 0,10);",
        "{}",
        "...range0To10"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Iterable supports currying. Calling the iterable will capture argument that is to be passed upon iterator query"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "const range = Iter.iterable(gener);",
        "const range0To5 = range(0,5);",
        "{}",
        "...range0To5"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Iterable also supports chaining itertools methods. When a method call is made with an iterttools method it creates a new pipelinecalls "
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "const filtered = Iter.iterable(Iter.filter(?));",
        "const seq = [1,2,3,4,5,10];",
        "const hs = filtered(seq, v => v%2==0).map(v=>v/2);",
        "{}",
        "...hs"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "The piplelien can be iterated multiple times. Each iteration makes a now iteration"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "...hs"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## observable"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### observeValue and onChange",
        "Similar to the old `observe` function but adheres to observe protocol. Namely, subscription is not passed as a parameter and lifetime is always controlled by the returning subscription. Also accepts next/error/complete listeners and by thus can be chained by other observer tools. Of course simple function are also accepts.",
        "",
        "observeValue passes each value change while onChange doesn't send the initial value (by default)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import {observeValue, onChange, bundleChanges} from \"system://core.observe\"",
        "",
        "class LogSubs {",
        "    msg = \"\"",
        "    next(...v) { console.log(this.msg, \": next:\", ??...v) }",
        "    error(e) { console.log(this.msg, \": error:\", ??e)}",
        "    complete() { console.log(this.msg, \": done\")}",
        "}",
        "const rec = #{ prop: \"alma\"};",
        "odict od { prop= \"first\"; bool= true}",
        "{}",
        "console.log(\"# onChange with unobservable should stop with error\");",
        "onChange(_=>rec.prop).subscribe(LogSubs{ msg=\"onChange/record\"});",
        "onChange(_=>??x.y).subscribe(LogSubs {msg=\"onChange/error\"});",
        "console.log(\"# observeValue with unobservable should deliver value and should complete\");",
        "observeValue(_=>rec.prop).subscribe(LogSubs{msg=\"observe/rec\"});",
        "observeValue(_=>??x.y).subscribe(LogSubs{msg=\"observe/error\"});",
        "console.log(\"# onChange only reports changes (when value is also changed). observe reports all values\");",
        "let s1 = observeValue(_ => od.prop).subscribe(LogSubs{msg=\"observe\"});",
        "let s2 = onChange(_ => od.prop).subscribe(LogSubs{msg=\"onChange\"});",
        "let s3 = onChange(_ => od.prop && od.bool).subscribe(LogSubs{msg=\"onChange of expression\"});",
        "let s4 = onChange(_ => {od.prop, od.bool}).subscribe(LogSubs{msg=\"multi value onChange\"});",
        "console.log(\"## Changing `prop`, should trigger `observe` and `onChange`\");",
        "od.prop = \"second\";",
        "console.log(\"## Changing `bool`, should trigger `onChange of expression`\");",
        "od.bool = false;",
        "console.log(\"## Dispose observeValue\");",
        "s1.cancel(); ",
        "console.log(\"## unchanged value should be ignored even in case of multivalue\");",
        "bundleChanges( _ => { invert od.bool; invert od.bool; });",
        "console.log(\"## Dispose all\");",
        "s2.cancel(); s3.cancel(); s4.cancel();",
        "od.prop = \"akarmi\"; od.bool=true;",
        ""
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### fromAsyncGen, fromGen, take(n)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import {fromAsyncGen, do as _do, take, lastValueFrom } from \"core://observe\"",
        "{}",
        "let s = fromAsyncGen(async function *() { yield 1; yield Promise.resolve(2); yield  3;} ) |> _do(v => console.log(\"value:\",v), ^) |> lastValueFrom(^);",
        "await s;",
        "//await fromAsyncGen(async function *() { yield 1; yield Promise.resolve(2); yield  3;} ) |> take(2, ^) |> _do(v => console.log(\"value:\",v), ^) |> lastValueFrom(^);"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import {do as _do, take, fromIter, fromGen, lastValueFrom } from \"core://observe\"",
        "{}",
        "let v1 = fromGen(function *() { yield 1; yield 20; yield  30;} ) |> take(2,^) |> _do(v => console.log(\"gen value:\",v), ^) |> lastValueFrom(^);",
        "console.log(await v1);",
        "let v2 = fromIter(function *() { yield 1; yield 20; yield  30;}() ) |> _do(v => console.log(\"iter value:\",v), ^) |> lastValueFrom(^);",
        "console.log(await v2);"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "class LogSubs {",
        "    msg = \"\"",
        "    next(...v) { console.log(this.msg, \": next:\", ??...v) }",
        "    error(e) { console.log(this.msg, \": error:\", ??e)}",
        "    complete() { console.log(this.msg, \": done\")}",
        "}",
        "import {do as _do, take, fromAsyncGen, fromGen, lastValueFrom,share } from \"core://observe\"",
        "{}",
        "let s = fromAsyncGen(async function *() { yield Promise.resolve(1); yield Promise.resolve(2); yield  3;} ) |> _do(v => console.log(\"value:\",v), ^) |> share(^);",
        "let v2 = take(2, s) |> _do(v => console.log(\"v2:\",v), ^) |> lastValueFrom(^);",
        "let v1 = take(1, s) |> _do(v => console.log(\"v1:\",v), ^)  |> lastValueFrom(^);",
        "let v3 = s |> _do(v => console.log(\"v3:\",v), ^) |> lastValueFrom(^);",
        "await.all([v1,v2,v3]);",
        ""
      ]
